data.name: help3.Text
data.value: 1. prepare folder with source tiles named "tileset_source" 2. inside this folder name images in format "image (N).png" N = (1 ... image count) 2.1 you can rename files to this format using shortcuts Ctrl+A; F2; write "image"; Enter on windows 3. Click button "Choose new tileset directory" to choose where to store tiles 4. set color snapping factor and tile size 5. Generate stone set

data.name: help4.Text
data.value: 1. chooose tileset folder 2. choose input photo 3. choose output location 4. set parameters 4.1. image scale = scale image before converting 4.2. snapping factor = 1 / color pallete size 4.3. tile size = same as in tileset 4.4. ignore black pixels = don't count black pixels to average 4.5. comparation = output image has reference to original 5. Create mozaic
